AGI - The former president of Uruguay Jose' Mujica (in office from 2010 to 2015) announced at a press conference that he had a tumor on the esophagus. "I must inform you that last Friday I went to Casmu hospital for a check, during which it was discovered that I have an esophagus tumor, > which is obviously very complicated and is double in my case, because I have been suffering from an immunological disease for more than 20 years," said the 88-year-old ex-president. He added that the disease also affected the kidneys, creating "obvious difficulties" for chemotherapy or surgery techniques. "All this is being evaluated by doctors, who are doing cell analysis, as this story continues. I want to tell you that in my life the sad reaper has passed more than once around my cot, but he has continued to make me a pastor in all these years," he emphasized the former president, specifying that this time you will have to see what will happen.
&nbsp;
The former president also said that as long as he can, he will continue to campaign alongside his comrades, faithful to his way of thinking, entertaining himself with his vegetables and his hens. "As long as I can resist, I'll be there. I want to thank them and convey to the young people of this country that life is beautiful and that is very fun". "The core of the matter to succeed in life is to start again every time you fall. And if there is anger, turn it into hope. Fight for love," said Mujica. Finally, he added that the only freedom that exists is in the head and is called "will". "If we don't use it, we're not free. And that must be understood. It is a challenge for the new generations. And life is so beautiful that it makes no sense to sacrifice it for stupid things. For the rest, I am grateful and, at the end of the day, I will be damned," he concluded.&nbsp;
